WEBVTT

01:46.640 --> 01:47.100
Xu Xiao.

01:47.280 --> 01:48.160
Eat more.

01:53.039 --> 01:54.640
Xu Xiao, you got into college.

01:54.640 --> 01:55.700
I bought a new phone

01:56.200 --> 01:56.759
for you.

01:59.920 --> 02:00.380
No need,

02:00.960 --> 02:01.560
thank you.

02:02.960 --> 02:03.440
No,

02:04.000 --> 02:05.640
the phone you were using before

02:05.640 --> 02:06.520
is an old model.

02:07.080 --> 02:08.639
I've told your mom several times

02:08.639 --> 02:09.900
that you need a new one.

02:10.840 --> 02:12.500
Just take it if he wants you to.

02:12.720 --> 02:14.380
I'll buy it myself if I need it.

02:15.000 --> 02:17.400
Where do you get money as a college student?

02:17.840 --> 02:18.680
I've checked.

02:19.240 --> 02:20.680
The living expenses I sent to your bank card,

02:20.680 --> 02:22.160
you haven't spent a cent of it.

02:22.160 --> 02:23.420
I have a part-time job.

02:24.079 --> 02:25.340
I can make my own money.

02:25.960 --> 02:27.620
Why are you being so stubborn?

02:28.560 --> 02:29.240
You're all grown up now.

02:29.240 --> 02:31.040
Can't you be a bit more sensible?

02:31.880 --> 02:32.940
And another thing,

02:33.120 --> 02:34.980
even if you refuse to call him Dad,

02:35.200 --> 02:37.060
you could at least call him Uncle.

02:38.800 --> 02:39.320
Well,

02:41.000 --> 02:42.560
let the child do whatever he is comfortable with.

02:42.560 --> 02:44.079
He can call me whatever he wants.

02:44.079 --> 02:44.640
Besides,

02:44.800 --> 02:46.520
the child is growing up.

02:46.600 --> 02:48.160
He wants to support himself.

02:48.160 --> 02:48.720
He is sensible.

02:48.720 --> 02:49.850
This is a good thing.

02:50.440 --> 02:51.120
Eat.

02:52.000 --> 02:53.130
Have a piece of meat.

02:54.600 --> 02:55.200
Eat more.

02:59.960 --> 03:01.560
I have something to tell you.

03:02.680 --> 03:04.600
Your uncle and I have discussed it.

03:04.600 --> 03:06.400
You will change your major in your sophomore year.

03:06.400 --> 03:07.600
After you finish this semester,

03:07.600 --> 03:09.130
we will apply to the school.

03:09.520 --> 03:10.000
Why?

03:11.960 --> 03:14.160
Your college entrance exam score was so high.

03:14.160 --> 03:15.360
You had many choices.

03:15.880 --> 03:18.520
But you insisted on choosing such an unpopular major.

03:18.520 --> 03:19.200
You...

03:19.200 --> 03:20.240
I like doing this.

03:22.880 --> 03:24.520
Do you think our family hasn't suffered enough

03:24.520 --> 03:25.450
because of this?

03:31.600 --> 03:33.400
You are exactly like that person.

03:33.400 --> 03:35.930
Always obsessed with those bottles and jars.

03:36.280 --> 03:37.000
Xu Xiao.

03:37.680 --> 03:39.079
I just don't understand.

03:39.560 --> 03:40.890
Your grades are so good.

03:41.560 --> 03:42.520
Why didn't you choose

03:42.520 --> 03:43.980
a major with a good future?

03:44.079 --> 03:46.140
Why must you follow his ruinous path?

03:46.640 --> 03:48.700
Kids grow up and have their own ideas.

03:48.800 --> 03:49.329
I'm full.

03:51.120 --> 03:52.050
I'm leaving now.

03:53.560 --> 03:54.220
Look at you.

03:54.240 --> 03:56.120
He acts like this just because I said a few words to him.

03:56.120 --> 03:57.000
We are eating.

03:57.000 --> 03:58.600
Just eat your food properly.

04:39.159 --> 04:39.760
Class.

04:40.800 --> 04:42.920
After the previous period of learning,

04:42.920 --> 04:44.120
you have all mastered

04:44.360 --> 04:46.490
the technical skills of restoration,

04:46.640 --> 04:49.000
and have acquired a certain level of restoration ability.

04:49.000 --> 04:51.080
Some of you have wanted to learn about

04:51.360 --> 04:52.960
porcelain restoration for a long time.

04:52.960 --> 04:54.520
Later, our old neighbors

04:54.640 --> 04:56.170
will bring their porcelain

04:56.360 --> 04:57.960
to communicate with you all.

04:58.600 --> 04:58.880
Okay.

04:58.880 --> 04:59.440
Mr. Yue,

04:59.840 --> 05:00.800
do you mean

05:00.800 --> 05:03.240
we should collect various old porcelain pieces here

05:03.240 --> 05:04.560
and then restore them?

05:04.600 --> 05:05.000
Yes.

05:05.960 --> 05:08.360
I've already talked to the neighbors here.

05:08.960 --> 05:10.320
They are all volunteering

05:10.320 --> 05:12.920
to support our teaching practice activities.

05:12.920 --> 05:13.840
But teacher,

05:14.240 --> 05:15.720
does he trust us?

05:16.080 --> 05:18.040
Isn't he afraid that novices like us

05:18.040 --> 05:19.440
will ruin his porcelain?

05:19.560 --> 05:20.890
Don't worry about that.

05:21.600 --> 05:22.920
Our old neighbors

05:23.160 --> 05:25.000
trust our school very much.

05:25.440 --> 05:26.920
At our Jingdezhen Ceramic University,

05:26.920 --> 05:28.160
the ceramic restoration of the cultural relic conservation major

05:28.160 --> 05:28.960
What's wrong?

05:29.080 --> 05:30.400
is very famous.

05:30.400 --> 05:32.640
I'm just a little nervous.

05:32.840 --> 05:34.600
I'm afraid I won't be able to fix the porcelain properly again.

05:34.600 --> 05:35.400
Be confident.

05:35.960 --> 05:36.960
You've already made a lot of progress.

05:36.960 --> 05:38.200
Everyone, please cherish the trust of the neighbors

05:38.200 --> 05:39.730
and the honor of the school.

05:40.040 --> 05:41.960
Come on, let's start getting ready.

05:41.960 --> 05:42.520
Come.

05:42.520 --> 05:43.120
Go.

05:43.640 --> 05:45.100
Over here. One group here.

05:45.120 --> 05:45.520
Okay.

05:46.000 --> 05:46.400
Come.

05:46.400 --> 05:47.120
Just this one.

05:47.120 --> 05:47.650
Any more?

05:51.080 --> 05:51.640
Young man.

05:51.640 --> 05:52.300
Hello, sir.

05:52.600 --> 05:54.130
Can this still be repaired?

05:55.240 --> 05:56.040
Young man,

05:56.800 --> 05:57.840
take a look for me.

05:58.080 --> 05:59.680
Can my Kangxi wucai piece

05:59.880 --> 06:00.940
still be restored?

06:01.440 --> 06:02.240
Just a moment.

06:03.240 --> 06:03.840
I'm sorry,

06:04.480 --> 06:05.680
but I think your piece

06:06.480 --> 06:07.410
is an imitation.

06:09.040 --> 06:10.570
What are you talking about?

06:10.920 --> 06:12.720
This is my family heirloom.

06:13.040 --> 06:15.600
Kangxi imperial kiln wucai porcelain has regular shapes.

06:15.600 --> 06:17.460
Yours looks more like a folk kiln.

06:17.480 --> 06:18.760
The foot ring edge is pointed,

06:18.760 --> 06:20.420
and there are patchy defects.

06:22.640 --> 06:23.960
What do you know?

06:24.200 --> 06:26.040
You are all undergrads.

06:26.360 --> 06:27.440
If you don't know how to repair it,

06:27.440 --> 06:28.240
just forget it.

06:28.240 --> 06:29.640
Imperial kiln porcelain has fine paste,

06:29.640 --> 06:30.570
white and solid,

06:30.720 --> 06:31.650
lustrous glaze,

06:32.040 --> 06:33.159
tight integration of paste and glaze,

06:33.159 --> 06:34.360
exquisite decoration,

06:34.360 --> 06:35.220
and neat marks.

06:35.760 --> 06:36.600
But your piece

06:37.159 --> 06:39.020
has rough paste and uneven glaze.

06:39.240 --> 06:40.520
The shape and decoration

06:40.520 --> 06:41.840
do not match the era.

06:43.120 --> 06:45.180
What this young man says makes sense.

06:45.240 --> 06:46.000
Your item

06:46.080 --> 06:47.480
doesn't look authentic.

06:49.000 --> 06:50.880
But we're not professional appraisers.

06:50.880 --> 06:52.000
Whether it's genuine or a replica,

06:52.000 --> 06:53.000
we can restore it.

06:53.320 --> 06:54.520
I won't fix it.

06:55.080 --> 06:56.280
If you won't fix it, leave.

06:56.280 --> 06:56.640
Here.

06:56.760 --> 06:57.360
Young man,

06:57.680 --> 07:00.040
what do you think of my cloud-dragon vase?

07:10.440 --> 07:11.800
This is amazing.

07:12.240 --> 07:13.640
It must be very valuable.

07:14.280 --> 07:15.240
It looks so good.

07:21.480 --> 07:21.840
Hello, auntie.

07:21.840 --> 07:22.200
Auntie,

07:22.200 --> 07:24.360
I heard you repair porcelain for free here.

07:24.360 --> 07:26.280
Yes, we are from Ceramic University.

07:26.280 --> 07:28.610
Could you take a look at this teapot for me?

07:29.280 --> 07:29.640
Okay.

07:32.080 --> 07:32.520
Auntie,

07:32.520 --> 07:34.120
what era is this teapot from?

07:34.159 --> 07:35.480
I can't remember clearly.

07:35.480 --> 07:37.240
It should be from the '60s.

07:37.760 --> 07:38.280
Auntie,

07:38.520 --> 07:40.000
we repair cultural relics here.

07:40.000 --> 07:40.880
This one

07:41.040 --> 07:42.080
looks quite new.

07:42.600 --> 07:44.680
There's probably no need to repair it.

07:44.680 --> 07:46.040
Whether it needs repairing,

07:46.040 --> 07:47.480
is it up to you to decide?

07:47.960 --> 07:50.020
If I knew you were going to be so picky,

07:50.240 --> 07:51.200
I wouldn't have come at all.

07:51.200 --> 07:52.200
Auntie, we really didn't mean that.

07:52.200 --> 07:53.400
We didn't say we wouldn't repair it.

07:53.400 --> 07:53.880
Okay.

07:54.000 --> 07:54.880
Auntie, in three days,

07:54.880 --> 07:55.600
right here,

07:55.800 --> 07:57.260
you can come and pick it up.

07:57.360 --> 07:57.960
All right.

08:07.480 --> 08:08.680
Everyone has

08:08.680 --> 08:10.280
porcelain to repair.

08:11.120 --> 08:12.280
Please be sure to

08:12.360 --> 08:14.040
take good care of them.

08:14.320 --> 08:15.000
You must repair them

08:15.000 --> 08:17.060
according to the clients' requests.

08:17.320 --> 08:19.480
During the next extracurricular practice class,

08:19.480 --> 08:21.680
we will return the repaired items.

08:21.760 --> 08:22.720
But I hope

08:22.920 --> 08:23.920
your work

08:24.000 --> 08:26.680
will meet the clients' expectations.

08:30.120 --> 08:32.380
I think my grandpa has a teapot like this.

08:32.679 --> 08:34.809
This is probably only worth 100 bucks.

08:34.880 --> 08:36.640
Why do I have to repair this?

08:36.840 --> 08:38.299
This Jian ware I'm fixing,

08:38.440 --> 08:39.919
with its color and texture,

08:39.919 --> 08:41.240
looks very valuable.

08:41.679 --> 08:42.679
What about yours?

08:42.880 --> 08:46.080
Yuexin and I have a porcelain horse from the Qing Dynasty.

08:46.400 --> 08:46.880
Look.

08:47.360 --> 08:48.560
The one Xu Xiao and his team have

08:48.560 --> 08:51.760
is a colorful cloud and dragon vase from the Ming Dynasty.

09:09.080 --> 09:09.760
Students.

09:10.120 --> 09:11.480
In a while, the neighbors

09:11.480 --> 09:12.610
will come to collect

09:12.680 --> 09:15.210
the porcelain they entrusted you to restore.

09:15.600 --> 09:16.320
We will

09:16.360 --> 09:18.560
base our evaluation on their satisfaction with the restored porcelain.

09:18.560 --> 09:19.680
I will grade you.

09:20.000 --> 09:21.200
Get ready, everyone.

09:21.760 --> 09:22.240
Come on.

09:23.560 --> 09:24.200
Take a look.

09:24.200 --> 09:24.840
Not bad.

09:25.120 --> 09:25.850
Just make do.

09:26.360 --> 09:27.600
This is too sloppy.

09:27.960 --> 09:28.880
How is it, miss?

09:29.080 --> 09:29.760
Is it fixed?

09:29.760 --> 09:30.440
You're here.

09:30.440 --> 09:30.960
You're here.

09:30.960 --> 09:32.960
This is what you brought in for repair.

09:32.960 --> 09:33.600
Take a look.

09:33.600 --> 09:35.330
This gluing is not good enough.

09:36.920 --> 09:37.720
Then I'll give it a try.

09:37.720 --> 09:38.880
Auntie Wu, you're here.

09:38.880 --> 09:39.520
Auntie Wu.

09:39.960 --> 09:41.280
Are my things fixed?

09:41.320 --> 09:41.800
Yes.

09:42.560 --> 09:43.220
Take a look.

09:46.320 --> 09:46.920
No.

09:47.320 --> 09:48.280
This won't do.

09:49.040 --> 09:50.000
Isn't it still usable?

09:50.000 --> 09:50.480
Yeah.

09:50.480 --> 09:51.240
It doesn't leak.

09:51.240 --> 09:52.600
You can still make tea with it.

09:52.600 --> 09:54.680
You just glued it together.

09:54.880 --> 09:56.040
How is this fixed?

09:56.440 --> 09:58.100
It's worse than not fixing it.

09:58.280 --> 09:58.920
No, Auntie Wu.

09:58.920 --> 09:59.320
We...

09:59.320 --> 10:01.240
This thing isn't worth much anyway.

10:01.240 --> 10:02.900
How do you talk to your elders?

10:02.920 --> 10:03.320
Auntie...

10:03.320 --> 10:04.200
What are your names?

10:04.200 --> 10:05.240
I'm going to find your teacher.

10:05.240 --> 10:05.760
No, no.

10:06.160 --> 10:07.690
You, come here. Both of you.

10:07.840 --> 10:08.880
Don't get excited.

10:08.880 --> 10:10.010
What's the problem?

10:10.280 --> 10:10.800
Look.

10:11.360 --> 10:12.600
Look at how they repaired it.

10:12.600 --> 10:13.930
I just have one request.

10:14.200 --> 10:16.360
Just make them repair it to look like it originally did.

10:16.360 --> 10:18.160
Auntie Wu's request is too high.

10:18.720 --> 10:19.840
It can't be repaired at all.

10:19.840 --> 10:21.480
We said back then that we couldn't take it.

10:21.480 --> 10:23.160
I'll have them take it back and redo it.

10:23.160 --> 10:25.560
Could you give the young people another chance?

10:25.560 --> 10:26.080
Fine.

10:26.360 --> 10:28.490
These young people nowadays, really.

10:28.560 --> 10:29.280
Take care.

10:32.280 --> 10:32.920
Mr. Liang.

10:34.240 --> 10:35.570
How about I give it a try?

10:35.600 --> 10:36.760
Mr. Liang, let him do it.

10:36.760 --> 10:38.320
It's so good to have you here.

10:38.320 --> 10:38.800
Xu Xiao,

10:39.080 --> 10:40.880
are you sure you want to take over for them

10:40.880 --> 10:42.000
and finish this restoration work?

10:42.000 --> 10:42.520
He's sure.

10:42.520 --> 10:43.050
I'm sure.

10:56.440 --> 10:58.800
Actually, I never quite understood

10:59.000 --> 11:00.200
what kind of restoration

11:00.200 --> 11:01.600
Auntie Wu really wanted.

11:02.680 --> 11:04.680
There are several types of restoration.

11:04.680 --> 11:07.040
There's restoration focused on functionality,

11:07.040 --> 11:09.440
restoration focused on visual presentation,

11:09.440 --> 11:11.920
and restoration that incorporates artistic enhancement.

11:11.920 --> 11:13.800
Lastly, there's the one we're familiar with,

11:13.800 --> 11:16.400
which is the conservation of cultural relics.

11:16.760 --> 11:18.080
Not everyone's purpose for restoration

11:18.080 --> 11:18.840
is the same.

11:20.040 --> 11:21.520
Does Auntie Wu think that

11:21.800 --> 11:23.720
filling the missing parts with plaster

11:23.720 --> 11:24.760
is too unsightly

11:25.480 --> 11:28.280
and completely different from what she imagined?

11:29.560 --> 11:30.520
Then try

11:30.880 --> 11:32.080
in the missing parts.

11:32.800 --> 11:34.730
Restore it with porcelain pieces.

11:35.760 --> 11:36.890
We first use plaster

11:37.080 --> 11:38.210
to make a prototype.

11:38.600 --> 11:39.680
Then we use porcelain clay

11:39.680 --> 11:40.940
to fire the fragments.

11:41.360 --> 11:42.280
We just need to consider

11:42.280 --> 11:45.010
the shrinkage ratio of the fragments in advance.

12:05.240 --> 12:05.800
Xiaocen.

12:06.440 --> 12:08.300
You have a good sense of patterns.

12:08.600 --> 12:10.260
The drawing and coloring work

12:10.640 --> 12:11.700
will be left to you.

12:23.320 --> 12:24.200
Why do we have to

12:24.200 --> 12:25.960
fire a new porcelain piece?

12:26.880 --> 12:28.040
Why don't we just use

12:28.040 --> 12:30.040
the resin we learned about in class

12:30.320 --> 12:32.440
and ceramics compensation material

12:32.440 --> 12:33.500
to make a new piece?

12:34.320 --> 12:36.320
Auntie Wu's teapot fragments are incomplete.

12:36.320 --> 12:38.200
It needs a large piece to fill the gap.

12:38.200 --> 12:38.800
Also,

12:39.160 --> 12:41.240
Auntie Wu's teapot is an everyday item

12:41.240 --> 12:42.840
and will be used frequently.

12:42.880 --> 12:43.880
So I decided

12:44.120 --> 12:46.000
to use the porcelain-to-porcelain repair method.

12:46.000 --> 12:47.530
Porcelain-to-porcelain?

12:47.880 --> 12:48.320
Yeah.

12:48.920 --> 12:50.240
This repair method

12:50.360 --> 12:52.440
is generally used on high-value fine items.

12:52.440 --> 12:55.200
It involves firing a porcelain piece identical to the original porcelain,

12:55.200 --> 12:56.360
selecting the right color and pattern,

12:56.360 --> 12:58.320
polishing and shaping it before adding color,

12:58.320 --> 13:01.380
and finally doing an overall color touch-up and aging.

13:02.800 --> 13:05.440
I didn't know there were so many details to consider.

13:05.440 --> 13:07.200
Since we accepted the commission,

13:07.200 --> 13:08.860
we have to do it the best we can.

13:13.840 --> 13:14.300
Come on.

13:15.080 --> 13:16.280
When we trim the base,

13:16.440 --> 13:17.900
we must be highly focused.

13:18.040 --> 13:19.760
And our hands must be steady.

13:20.000 --> 13:21.000
Watch carefully.

13:24.240 --> 13:25.300
Isn't this Xu Xiao?

13:25.880 --> 13:26.540
Uncle Wang.

13:27.400 --> 13:30.060
I would like you to fire a porcelain piece for me.

13:31.120 --> 13:32.450
What do you want to fire?

13:32.600 --> 13:33.260
Right here.

13:34.800 --> 13:35.460
Take a look.

13:41.640 --> 13:42.800
Is it for filling a gap?

13:42.800 --> 13:43.120
Yes.

13:43.800 --> 13:44.200
Okay.

13:44.360 --> 13:46.120
I will fire a batch of porcelain tonight.

13:46.120 --> 13:47.920
You two can come get it tomorrow.

13:47.920 --> 13:48.800
Thank you, Uncle Wang.

13:48.800 --> 13:49.720
Thank you, Uncle Wang.

13:49.720 --> 13:50.380
No problem.

13:52.520 --> 13:53.200
Hu.

13:53.560 --> 13:56.020
Thank you for helping me burn Qing last time.

13:56.320 --> 13:57.120
Miss,

13:57.120 --> 13:58.520
what are you talking about?

13:58.520 --> 13:59.650
I don't understand.

14:02.920 --> 14:03.840
Miss,

14:03.840 --> 14:06.170
isn't this the first time we've met today?

14:06.800 --> 14:07.600
You kid,

14:07.720 --> 14:09.720
what did you do behind my back again?

14:10.400 --> 14:11.320
Um, Uncle Wang,

14:12.000 --> 14:13.160
we won't bother you anymore.

14:13.160 --> 14:14.290
We'll go back first.

14:15.080 --> 14:16.480
See you tomorrow. Thank you, Uncle Wang.

14:16.480 --> 14:17.680
It's fine, it's fine.

14:18.240 --> 14:18.880
Continue.

14:19.360 --> 14:21.080
Look, we changed a tool.

15:16.000 --> 15:16.480
Here.

15:21.520 --> 15:22.160
Hello.

15:23.040 --> 15:24.040
Who are you?

15:24.160 --> 15:24.800
Hello.

15:25.040 --> 15:25.900
It's like this.

15:26.480 --> 15:28.120
We are students from

15:28.120 --> 15:29.880
Jingdezhen Ceramic University majoring in Cultural Relics Conservation.

15:29.880 --> 15:31.740
In our previous practical class,

15:31.760 --> 15:34.400
Auntie Wu entrusted us to help her restore porcelain.

15:34.400 --> 15:36.000
Here, have some water first.

15:36.120 --> 15:36.720
Thank you.

15:38.000 --> 15:40.000
Good thing I came back to get something today,

15:40.000 --> 15:42.060
or you'd have made a trip for nothing.

15:44.000 --> 15:46.240
Does Auntie Wu usually live here alone?

15:47.200 --> 15:48.860
This is my family's old house.

15:49.120 --> 15:50.480
After my grandpa passed away,

15:50.480 --> 15:52.040
I got married and moved out too.

15:52.040 --> 15:53.570
Now my mom lives here alone.

15:53.800 --> 15:55.730
What did my mom give you to restore?

16:01.160 --> 16:02.480
This teapot,

16:03.000 --> 16:03.800
I remember it.

16:04.520 --> 16:05.960
When I was cleaning the room last month,

16:05.960 --> 16:07.360
I accidentally broke it.

16:08.000 --> 16:09.800
But I remember throwing it in the trash.

16:09.800 --> 16:11.400
Why did she take it out again?

16:11.640 --> 16:13.970
Auntie Wu seems to value this teapot a lot.

16:14.160 --> 16:15.840
But my mom doesn't usually drink tea.

16:15.840 --> 16:17.300
I've never seen her use it.

16:17.840 --> 16:20.040
She didn't give you a hard time, did she?

16:21.280 --> 16:24.120
My mom's temper has been getting worse these past few years.

16:24.120 --> 16:25.360
I come home to see her now,

16:25.360 --> 16:27.160
and she still gets angry with me.

16:31.800 --> 16:32.440
Auntie Wu.

16:35.000 --> 16:36.530
Why did you come to my house?

16:36.920 --> 16:37.640
Auntie Wu,

16:38.240 --> 16:40.240
we've fixed your teapot for you.

16:45.480 --> 16:47.140
The previously damaged parts

16:47.320 --> 16:48.720
we have re-fired,

16:49.920 --> 16:51.400
along with the signs of wear.

16:51.400 --> 16:52.440
We kept it too.

17:02.280 --> 17:04.140
If the teapot is broken, let it be.

17:04.200 --> 17:05.680
I can just buy you a new one.

17:06.119 --> 17:08.319
Why did you pick it back out of the trash?

17:11.240 --> 17:11.800
Mom.

17:12.280 --> 17:13.680
Say something, at least.

17:14.000 --> 17:15.920
These two students have been waiting for you for ages.

17:15.920 --> 17:17.720
You're the only polite one here.

17:17.839 --> 17:18.480
Besides,

17:18.680 --> 17:19.880
they volunteered.

17:20.280 --> 17:21.599
I didn't beg them to.

17:22.119 --> 17:23.920
Mom, how can you say that?

17:23.920 --> 17:25.599
We should at least thank them.

17:26.240 --> 17:27.240
Auntie Wu,

17:28.359 --> 17:31.160
are you not satisfied with our restoration?

17:32.440 --> 17:34.240
Does it matter if I'm satisfied?

17:35.160 --> 17:36.760
As long as you're satisfied.

17:41.280 --> 17:42.800
I'm really sorry.

17:43.240 --> 17:44.880
My mom's temper is just like this.

17:44.880 --> 17:46.540
Please don't take it to heart.

17:46.760 --> 17:47.440
It seems Auntie Wu

17:47.440 --> 17:49.840
still thinks we didn't do a good enough job.

17:50.160 --> 17:51.320
Not really.

17:51.960 --> 17:52.760
This teapot,

17:54.400 --> 17:55.800
can we take it back again?

17:56.200 --> 17:56.960
Of course.

18:07.440 --> 18:08.720
I really don't understand

18:08.720 --> 18:10.520
what Auntie Wu actually wants.

18:11.600 --> 18:13.530
There must be something we missed.

18:34.080 --> 18:34.560
Sir,

18:35.120 --> 18:36.050
how much is this?

18:38.400 --> 18:39.000
Handsome.

18:39.800 --> 18:40.400
Handsome.

18:41.320 --> 18:42.000
Coming,

18:42.240 --> 18:43.000
my customer.

18:43.560 --> 18:44.480
You called me handsome,

18:44.480 --> 18:45.400
so I'm coming.

18:45.640 --> 18:46.040
No.

18:46.520 --> 18:47.680
Why is he ignoring me?

18:47.680 --> 18:48.640
He ignores you,

18:48.640 --> 18:49.440
but I'm not.

18:49.560 --> 18:50.240
What do you need?

18:50.240 --> 18:50.800
Buying or selling?

18:50.800 --> 18:51.880
Is he your employee?

18:51.880 --> 18:52.480
Of course.

18:52.640 --> 18:53.840
You even hire someone like him?

18:53.840 --> 18:55.170
Mind your own business.

18:55.280 --> 18:56.940
I'm not in the mood. Forget it.

18:58.800 --> 19:01.000
Does Auntie Wu usually live here alone?

19:01.160 --> 19:02.800
This is our family's old house.

19:02.800 --> 19:04.120
After my grandpa passed away,

19:04.120 --> 19:05.850
I got married and moved out too.

19:15.240 --> 19:16.960
But my mom doesn't usually drink tea.

19:16.960 --> 19:18.420
I've never seen her use it.

19:20.280 --> 19:21.640
Look at how they fixed it.

19:21.640 --> 19:22.970
I just have one request.

19:23.160 --> 19:25.240
I want it restored to how it was.

19:32.160 --> 19:32.760
Xiaocen,

19:33.200 --> 19:36.060
send me the photo of the teapot before it was broken.

19:51.720 --> 19:52.240
Hello?

19:52.440 --> 19:53.240
Are you at home?

19:53.240 --> 19:54.170
I'm downstairs.

19:55.400 --> 19:56.680
Bring the teapot with you now.

19:56.680 --> 19:58.340
I'll wait for you downstairs.

20:05.560 --> 20:07.040
Mom, I'm going out for a bit.

20:07.040 --> 20:08.200
You're still going out this late?

20:08.200 --> 20:08.600
Yes.

20:11.400 --> 20:12.440
Did you bring the pot?

20:12.440 --> 20:13.170
I brought it.

20:13.480 --> 20:14.210
I think I know

20:14.760 --> 20:16.080
why Auntie Wu is angry.

20:17.320 --> 20:17.840
Let's go.

20:17.840 --> 20:18.440
Follow me.

20:34.840 --> 20:36.120
I'm really sorry.

20:36.440 --> 20:37.960
My mom is just like that.

20:38.360 --> 20:39.620
Sorry for the trouble.

20:40.080 --> 20:40.680
It's okay.

20:41.520 --> 20:42.320
I understand.

20:55.240 --> 20:55.840
Auntie Wu.

20:56.960 --> 20:57.960
I am really sorry.

20:59.160 --> 21:00.820
Our skills are not good enough

21:01.560 --> 21:03.080
to do a seamless repair

21:03.440 --> 21:05.500
and restore it to its original state.

21:06.840 --> 21:08.120
We have tried our best to restore it

21:08.120 --> 21:10.380
to the appearance you are familiar with.

21:10.840 --> 21:12.500
I just hope you can take a look.

22:02.840 --> 22:04.680
Alright, stop crying.

22:05.280 --> 22:06.600
It's just a bump,

22:07.160 --> 22:08.680
it's not a big problem.

22:09.680 --> 22:11.540
I'll show you a magic trick later,

22:11.560 --> 22:12.200
okay?

22:12.880 --> 22:13.480
Come here.

22:19.960 --> 22:22.020
Dad is going to show you a magic trick.

22:24.720 --> 22:25.360
Here.

22:28.800 --> 22:30.400
A little gap.

22:30.400 --> 22:31.760
Ta-da.

22:36.120 --> 22:36.920
Look.

22:37.200 --> 22:39.120
Hasn't it become the character 'Wu'?

22:39.120 --> 22:39.840
Right?

22:41.640 --> 22:42.200
Done.

22:43.000 --> 22:44.460
It's all fixed now, right?

22:54.440 --> 22:55.000
Done.

23:06.560 --> 23:07.720
It's okay, Mom.

23:14.240 --> 23:15.160
Thank you.

23:20.800 --> 23:21.600
Alright, Mom.

23:22.240 --> 23:23.120
Don't be sad.

23:26.560 --> 23:27.960
It's all in the past, Mom.

23:38.760 --> 23:39.600
Xu Xiao,

23:40.480 --> 23:41.810
you are really amazing.

23:42.320 --> 23:43.840
How did you find out back then

23:43.840 --> 23:46.440
that there was a secret at the bottom of the pot?

23:46.720 --> 23:47.440
Actually,

23:48.200 --> 23:50.130
when I first started repairing it,

23:50.520 --> 23:53.380
I had already seen the marks at the bottom of the pot.

23:53.400 --> 23:56.560
At that time, I also thought they were just ordinary scratches.

23:56.560 --> 23:58.290
Later, on the wall of her house,

23:59.360 --> 24:00.890
I saw Mr. Wu's calligraphy.

24:02.000 --> 24:02.560
I figured

24:03.320 --> 24:04.380
Auntie Wu's father

24:05.600 --> 24:07.000
must be a playful person.

24:08.640 --> 24:10.840
Thank you for helping Auntie Wu get back

24:10.840 --> 24:12.300
such beautiful memories.

24:13.960 --> 24:15.020
We did it together.

24:20.760 --> 24:22.560
Actually, I was thinking about

24:23.320 --> 24:25.560
why Auntie Wu was so angry.

24:26.240 --> 24:28.160
It's because this porcelain

24:28.440 --> 24:31.700
carries all the little moments between her and her family.

24:32.240 --> 24:33.920
But this beautiful feeling

24:34.080 --> 24:35.640
seems to be fading away.

24:36.800 --> 24:37.640
I think

24:38.560 --> 24:40.720
the opposite of life isn't death,

24:41.640 --> 24:43.240
but rather being forgotten.

24:43.480 --> 24:44.680
So I feel that

24:44.680 --> 24:46.640
we're not just helping them

24:46.720 --> 24:47.880
repair porcelain.

24:48.280 --> 24:49.340
More importantly,

24:49.760 --> 24:52.490
we're repairing the beauty behind the porcelain

24:52.720 --> 24:53.720
and the memories.

24:58.160 --> 25:00.020
We can only live for a few decades,

25:00.640 --> 25:02.840
yet we can fight against infinite time.

25:04.240 --> 25:05.280
Isn't that interesting?
